(80, 1, '2025-03-29 19:47:25', '2025-03-29 08:47:25', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Why We Choose Organic: Gardening the Natural Way</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":238,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress_2/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/image-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-238\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Going organic isn’t just a trend—it’s a commitment to creating gardens that are safe for people, pets, and the planet. We avoid synthetic pesticides and fertilizers in favor of natural alternatives that enrich the soil and protect pollinators like bees and butterflies. Organic gardening also means embracing biodiversity. From companion planting to welcoming beneficial insects, we take a holistic approach that supports the entire ecosystem. The result? Beautiful, resilient gardens that thrive with minimal intervention.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:post-date /-->', 'Blog 1', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'blog-1', '', '', '2025-04-10 20:32:41', '2025-04-10 10:32:41', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=80', 0, 'post', '', 0),
