(221, 1, '2025-04-06 01:10:30', '2025-04-05 14:10:30', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>The Secret to Thriving Gardens: It Starts with the Soil</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":102,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/index-image3-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-102\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When it comes to gardening, soil is everything. Healthy soil provides the essential nutrients, structure, and moisture plants need to grow. But not all soil is created equal. That’s why we focus on using rich, organic compost and high-quality soil blends that support plant health from the roots up.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Improving your soil can be as simple as adding organic matter, like compost or aged manure, and avoiding harsh chemicals that strip away beneficial microbes. Over time, you\'ll notice stronger plant growth, better water retention, and fewer pests. Healthy soil truly is the heart of a healthy garden.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:post-date /-->', 'Blog 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '99-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-04-06 01:10:30', '2025-04-05 14:10:30', '', 99, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=221', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(222, 1, '2025-04-06 01:11:13', '2025-04-05 14:11:13', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Why We Choose Organic: Gardening the Natural Way</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":87,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/pexels-cottonbro-4503732-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-87\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Going organic isn’t just a trend—it’s a commitment to creating gardens that are safe for people, pets, and the planet. We avoid synthetic pesticides and fertilizers in favor of natural alternatives that enrich the soil and protect pollinators like bees and butterflies.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Organic gardening also means embracing biodiversity. From companion planting to welcoming beneficial insects, we take a holistic approach that supports the entire ecosystem. The result? Beautiful, resilient gardens that thrive with minimal intervention.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:post-date /-->', 'Blog 1', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '80-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-04-06 01:11:13', '2025-04-05 14:11:13', '', 80, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=222', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(224, 1, '2025-04-06 01:11:43', '2025-04-05 14:11:43', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Why We Choose Organic: Gardening the Natural Way</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":87,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/pexels-cottonbro-4503732-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-87\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Going organic isn’t just a trend—it’s a commitment to creating gardens that are safe for people, pets, and the planet. We avoid synthetic pesticides and fertilizers in favor of natural alternatives that enrich the soil and protect pollinators like bees and butterflies. Organic gardening also means embracing biodiversity. From companion planting to welcoming beneficial insects, we take a holistic approach that supports the entire ecosystem. The result? Beautiful, resilient gardens that thrive with minimal intervention.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:post-date /-->', 'Blog 1', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '80-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-04-06 01:11:43', '2025-04-05 14:11:43', '', 80, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=224', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(225, 1, '2025-04-06 01:12:06', '2025-04-05 14:12:06', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>The Secret to Thriving Gardens: It Starts with the Soil</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":102,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/index-image3-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-102\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When it comes to gardening, soil is everything. Healthy soil provides the essential nutrients, structure, and moisture plants need to grow. But not all soil is created equal. That’s why we focus on using rich, organic compost and high-quality soil blends that support plant health from the roots up. Improving your soil can be as simple as adding organic matter, like compost or aged manure, and avoiding harsh chemicals that strip away beneficial microbes. Over time, you\'ll notice stronger plant growth, better water retention, and fewer pests. Healthy soil truly is the heart of a healthy garden.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:post-date /-->', 'Blog 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '99-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-04-06 01:12:06', '2025-04-05 14:12:06', '', 99, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=225', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
